parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive engine heat can cause discomfort, distraction, and even first-degree burns to the rider, particularly in slow-speed or heavy traffic situations. This can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially if the rider needs to make sudden maneuvers or is unable to control the motorcycle.
symptoms: Excessive heat emanating from the engine
and burns on the upper thigh; motorcycle becomes undrivable at slow speeds or in heavy traffic; engine dies or stalls due to overheating; need to pull over to let the engine cool off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause brake fluid to leak, leading to a loss of brake function, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid weeps out of the master cylinder
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Failure Due to Fuse Blown
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of headlights while driving can cause a significant reduction in visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on dark roads.
symptoms: the vehicle's headlight switch is flipped but the lights do not turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud noise when shifting into fifth gear can be a distraction to the rider, potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Loud noise when shifting into fifth gear
unusual sounds or vibrations when operating the motorcycle.
